In the Generative AI ecosystem, RAG (which stands for Retrieval-Augmented Generation) is a technology that stops an AI from guessing or making up facts by letting it look up the right information from an outside source before it answers you.
Think of a normal AI like a student taking a closed-book exam using only what they remember, while an AI with RAG is like a student taking an open-book exam with a massive library right in front of them.
For example, if you ask a regular AI, "What is my company's new office leave policy for this year?", it won't know because that private data wasn't part of its public training. A RAG system solves this by quickly searching your company's private files, finding the exact policy document and feeding it to the AI so it can read it and write a perfectly accurate, up-to-date answer for you.  
